data.content:
## What breaks

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider allowed synchronous LINQ via an explicit opt-in (`AllowSynchronousIO`). **In .NET 11 (EF Core 11), that opt-in is removed entirely.** All four of your synchronous calls — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` — will throw `InvalidOperationException` at runtime with no workaround.

The Cosmos DB provider only supports async I/O now.

## How to fix

Convert every method to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
- Return types → `Task<T>` / `Task`
- Methods marked `async`, renamed with `Async` suffix
- `ToList` → `ToListAsync`, `First` → `FirstAsync`, `Count` → `CountAsync`, `SaveChanges` → `SaveChangesAsync`

You'll also need to propagate `async/await` up through all callers (controllers, services, etc.) — async is "contagious."
